/*
Problem: Number of Unique XOR Triplets I
Difficulty: Medium
Topic: Bit Manipulation, Math

Approach:
- The array is nums = [1, 2, ..., n].
- If n < 3:
    - There are fewer than three elements, so every possible XOR result
      is simply one of the existing numbers.
- Otherwise:
    - Let k be the number of bits required to represent n.
    - Every XOR value from 0 to (2^k - 1) can be formed by some triplet.
    - Hence, the answer is exactly 2^k.

Time Complexity: O(1)
Space Complexity: O(1)
*/

class Solution {
public:
    int uniqueXorTriplets(int n) {
        if (n < 3)
            return n;

        int bits = 32 - __builtin_clz(n);
        return 1 << bits;
    }
};
